# Git Identity Guardrail (Windows)

- Prefer running `git commit` in PowerShell on Windows.
- Before committing, verify identity in the active shell:
  - `git config --get user.name`
  - `git config --get user.email`
- If either value is empty, do not commit until identity is explicit.
- When committing from bash or a non-default shell, use one-shot identity:
  - `git -c user.name="..." -c user.email="..." commit ...`
- Do not modify global git config during automated task flow.
- If shell identity and expected identity differ, stop and ask the user.
